shortly after taking office , president kennedy decided that southwest washington , a 99 % black neighborhood , was an eyesore and ought to be torn down .
by decree befitting his position of undisputed royalty , the entire area , including the popular waterfront restaurant district , but excluding 3 historic churches ; was reduced to rubble .
black residents evicted from their homes relocated as best they could , and without federal assistance ; likewise businesses were simply put out of business , few re - locating .
