in a strange way , also , i found the story to be another take on the ostentation of royalty i 'd noticed in curse of the golden flower and marie antoinette , both of which i 'd seen just prior , although shakti of course is an entirely different kind of film ; but the focus on a dysfunctional royal family  here living in the austerity of terrorism - controlled poverty in india rather than the elegance of versailles or the massive megalomania of feudal china 's tang dynasty  whose self - serving seeking of power brings ruin upon many others and forces an uprising of one kind or another provides the film with a notable subtext .
