but i found in this film an austere , powerful , spontaneous and entirely convincing voice of protest from the women who kept the vigil outside the place on rosenstrasse where their jewish relatives and others were detained .
i found nothing flashy , contemporary or manipulative in this depiction .
the very absence of extreme violence ( no one is shot or otherwise physically brutalized ) intensified my tension , which increased incrementally as the film progressed .
you keep waiting for some vicious attack to begin any minute .
