but as this is a formula picture , not a strindberg play , the possibility that stanwyck might want want to have a fling,--leaving aside the question of her husband 's predicament,--remains unexplored .
in this sense the incoming tide does n't quite have the effect one might have wished , though the movie remains tense and highly entertaining thanks to excellent acting , fine location photography , nearly all of it outdoors , and excellent direction by the woefully underrated mr. sturges .
