shakespeare behind bars was the most surprising and delightful film i 've seen all year .
it 's about a prison program , somewhere in california if i recall correctly , where the inmates have rehearsed and performed a different shakespeare play every year for the past 14 years .
the film follows their production of " the tempest " from casting through performance , and in the process we learn some pretty amazing things about these men , who are all in for the most serious of crimes .
